Ghanaian rapper Sarkodie has said he has returned to the gym after receiving inspiration from Afropop Davido. The 36-year-old Tema-born rapper shared a video of him working out in the gym crediting Davido for the decision. Upon signing a massive deal with the global sports brand, PUMA, the DMW boss began a workout regime and consistently followed it through.   Olamide welcomes Jayboi, Asake to YBNL     Why my marriage didn’t work, by Mo Abudu     Carryovers won’t stop me from getting varsity degree – Bella…   His decision to keep fit has also rubbed off on others around and beyond as he had shared a video that also captured Small Doctor at his during one of his workout sessions alongside his 30 BG crew. - Advertisement - Recently, Tiwa Savage also shared similar workout video. Sharing his workout video, Sarkodi wrote: “Been lazy but Davido inspired me. Let’s go brother.”